1
00:00:14,384 --> 00:00:19,822
<i>Connecting old words</i>
<i>that have been used up</i>

2
00:00:20,657 --> 00:00:28,564
<i>I just want to convey</i>
<i>my simple thoughts</i>

3
00:00:28,631 --> 00:00:34,001
<i>That day's faint wind blows away</i>

4
00:00:34,070 --> 00:00:38,131
<i>at the castle ruins of yesterday</i>

5
00:00:39,375 --> 00:00:44,278
<i>I'll laugh with you</i>
<i>and live for the moment</i>

6
00:00:45,014 --> 00:00:51,920
<i>Still that incident</i>
<i>will continue to trouble you, right?</i>

7
00:00:53,323 --> 00:00:56,815
<i>That's why it must be good bye</i>

8
00:00:56,893 --> 00:01:03,799
<i>Leaving nothing behind,</i>
<i>let us share what is left</i>

9
00:01:03,933 --> 00:01:10,998
<i>In time, we'll realize</i>
<i>that it was everything</i>

10
00:01:11,074 --> 00:01:17,741
<i>And sadness will touch our cheeks,</i>
<i>creating a river of tears</i>

11
00:01:18,147 --> 00:01:27,715
<i>Trembling thoughts swept into a vortex</i>
<i>and melting away</i>

12
00:01:31,271 --> 00:01:32,465
<i>That form...?!</i>

13
00:02:13,947 --> 00:02:18,407
So that's the extent of
the rumored "Absolute Defense?"

14
00:02:23,156 --> 00:02:24,521
How disappointing.

15
00:02:34,868 --> 00:02:38,065
I see... You were wearing sand, eh?

16
00:02:38,872 --> 00:02:40,464
Your opponent's not just him!

17
00:02:40,907 --> 00:02:42,135
I'm here, too!

18
00:03:01,261 --> 00:03:02,558
<i>Th-That attack just now...</i>

19
00:03:02,629 --> 00:03:05,860
<i>It would've been dangerous</i>
<i>had I not been protected by sand.</i>

20
00:03:08,068 --> 00:03:10,696
<i>M-My body is still...</i>

21
00:03:12,439 --> 00:03:15,169
<i>I'll just be a hindrance like this.</i>

22
00:03:18,278 --> 00:03:20,041
Annoying sand...

23
00:03:21,214 --> 00:03:23,739
You're first, Gaara.

24
00:03:44,871 --> 00:03:47,101
<i>He yanked out his spinal column?!</i>

25
00:03:50,610 --> 00:03:55,604
<i>Vengeful Strike.</i>
<i>The Bracken Dance</i>

26
00:04:01,721 --> 00:04:03,689
Dance of the Clematis Flower.

27
00:04:03,990 --> 00:04:04,820
Vine!

28
00:04:16,469 --> 00:04:17,401
Flower!

29
00:04:23,776 --> 00:04:25,801
A bone of the strongest calcification...

30
00:04:27,647 --> 00:04:31,845
It will pierce you,
sand defense and all...

31
00:04:33,453 --> 00:04:34,715
<i>No time...huh?</i>

32
00:04:42,195 --> 00:04:45,426
Ultimate Defense: Shukaku's Shield!

33
00:04:55,241 --> 00:04:56,401
Kabuto...

34
00:04:56,843 --> 00:04:59,437
How much longer will
Kimimaro hold out for?

35
00:04:59,979 --> 00:05:02,777
I think he should still
be okay for a while...

36
00:05:05,785 --> 00:05:08,151
I did all I could with the treatment...

37
00:05:08,888 --> 00:05:12,654
But there's not nearly enough
information about his body.

38
00:05:14,360 --> 00:05:17,693
I think it'd be quite different
if we had something

39
00:05:17,764 --> 00:05:20,358
like the medical history
and treatment data of his clan.

40
00:05:23,002 --> 00:05:24,731
What came out after looking into it

41
00:05:24,804 --> 00:05:33,678
was the bloody history of how
the Kaguya Clan became just him...

42
00:05:41,588 --> 00:05:45,649
Fools who provoked the great land of
the Village Hidden in the Mist into battle

43
00:05:45,725 --> 00:05:47,716
with just their clan
and were annihilated.

44
00:05:51,064 --> 00:05:55,433
The Kaguya Clan was
a foolish clan that liked battle.

45
00:05:56,202 --> 00:06:00,536
The battlefield was the only place
where they could be at peace.

46
00:06:01,507 --> 00:06:04,203
But it was long ago when
a simple minded group

47
00:06:04,277 --> 00:06:07,906
that only enjoyed slaughter
was acceptable...

48
00:06:08,615 --> 00:06:10,549
The times are different now.

49
00:06:11,317 --> 00:06:14,878
Doing something like fighting
only with power

50
00:06:14,954 --> 00:06:17,582
against a governed organization
like the Mist...

51
00:06:17,657 --> 00:06:21,855
can only be called an act of fools
rushing towards death.

52
00:06:23,863 --> 00:06:27,321
And then you saved only he
who was the youngest

53
00:06:27,400 --> 00:06:31,564
and the most exceptional
among the Kaguya Clan...

54
00:06:35,141 --> 00:06:40,306
That kid possessed the power that
would be feared even by the fighting clan.

55
00:06:40,913 --> 00:06:44,508
So it seems he was kept
in prison the whole time.

56
00:06:45,485 --> 00:06:48,283
It would've been a waste to let him... die.

57
00:06:49,255 --> 00:06:53,214
Who wouldn't want
that rare Kekkei Genkai?

58
00:06:54,394 --> 00:06:56,589
He possesses a strong
and firm bone structure

59
00:06:56,663 --> 00:07:00,155
and a defensive power to
repel all kinds of physical attacks.

60
00:07:01,034 --> 00:07:03,901
And if turned to offense...

61
00:07:04,337 --> 00:07:07,431
the bones become
a most powerful weapon.

62
00:07:19,018 --> 00:07:21,384
<i>It's because I've fought him once</i>
<i>that I understand this.</i>

63
00:07:21,454 --> 00:07:24,719
<i>That sand shield is</i>
<i>an absolute defense, no less.</i>

64
00:07:24,957 --> 00:07:27,551
<i>And that unusual form...</i>

65
00:07:27,627 --> 00:07:29,857
<i>It'll be okay.</i>
<i>There's no way it'll be broken!</i>

66
00:08:09,469 --> 00:08:10,436
It's hard...

67
00:08:11,170 --> 00:08:14,264
I gathered minerals with
great hardness from the ground,

68
00:08:14,340 --> 00:08:18,174
applied pressure with Chakra
and mixed them into the sand.

69
00:08:27,120 --> 00:08:30,920
You... that unusual Jutsu...

70
00:08:31,557 --> 00:08:33,252
It's the Kekkei Genkai, right?

71
00:08:34,360 --> 00:08:35,827
The Kaguya Clan...

72
00:08:36,763 --> 00:08:40,460
The ability which now
only I possess.

73
00:08:40,800 --> 00:08:42,995
The last one of the clan, eh?

74
00:08:43,603 --> 00:08:47,505
Then it'll die out here today.

75
00:08:48,074 --> 00:08:50,338
Indeed, that might happen.

76
00:08:51,411 --> 00:08:55,370
Due to sickness,
my body will not last so long...

77
00:08:56,516 --> 00:09:00,384
But, the clan will not die out.

78
00:09:03,356 --> 00:09:06,382
Besides I'm not alone.

79
00:09:17,069 --> 00:09:19,401
This is the "Earth" Curse Mark...

80
00:09:20,173 --> 00:09:21,037
With this...

81
00:09:21,507 --> 00:09:23,566
I can become a part of you,
Lord Orochimaru.

82
00:09:24,844 --> 00:09:28,007
Let's get everything, Kimimaro.

83
00:09:28,548 --> 00:09:32,450
And let's see the truth of
this world together.

84
00:09:33,453 --> 00:09:34,351
Yes.

85
00:09:35,054 --> 00:09:37,682
You're my "Vessel of Dreams."

86
00:09:38,991 --> 00:09:40,356
I'm counting on you.

87
00:09:41,994 --> 00:09:46,431
They are presents from me.
I hope you like them.

88
00:09:58,611 --> 00:10:03,947
Would you rather... die or obey?

89
00:10:04,450 --> 00:10:05,781
Obey...

90
00:10:06,018 --> 00:10:07,383
You will!

91
00:10:23,803 --> 00:10:26,829
Is this the best a team
of four can do?

92
00:10:30,243 --> 00:10:32,507
I'll ask just once more...

93
00:10:33,513 --> 00:10:34,946
Which would you rather choose?

94
00:10:40,887 --> 00:10:42,149
Very well...

95
00:10:42,455 --> 00:10:45,015
As of now, we're the Sound Ninja Five.

96
00:10:52,798 --> 00:10:54,527
Not alone, you said?

97
00:10:54,901 --> 00:10:55,629
That's right...

98
00:10:56,502 --> 00:11:00,632
As an existence shouldering
one part of Lord Orochimaru's ambition...

99
00:11:03,309 --> 00:11:06,472
I will remain inside
Lord Orochimaru's soul...

100
00:11:06,546 --> 00:11:08,639
for all eternity.

101
00:11:09,849 --> 00:11:12,443
Orochimaru's brainwashing, huh...?

102
00:11:13,953 --> 00:11:15,420
You're a pitiful guy.

103
00:11:26,433 --> 00:11:30,233
<i>I used my big moves too much.</i>
<i>I don't have much Chakra.</i>

104
00:11:30,737 --> 00:11:31,999
<i>This is the last of it.</i>

105
00:11:41,014 --> 00:11:42,777
What an amount of Chakra...

106
00:11:54,494 --> 00:11:55,927
You are something...

107
00:12:01,468 --> 00:12:04,960
I'll sink and confine you
200 meters into the ground.

108
00:12:05,539 --> 00:12:08,565
By the pressure of the sand
stuck to your body,

109
00:12:08,642 --> 00:12:11,440
you'll soon be unable to move,
not even a finger...

110
00:12:25,759 --> 00:12:29,286
You did it...!
This time for sure you did it.

111
00:12:38,505 --> 00:12:39,995
Dance...

112
00:12:41,341 --> 00:12:42,968
Bracken Dance!

113
00:13:05,766 --> 00:13:07,324
It is annoying...

114
00:13:08,869 --> 00:13:11,269
It feels like a long time

115
00:13:11,338 --> 00:13:13,636
when waiting eagerly for
something you want.

116
00:13:14,141 --> 00:13:15,005
Kabuto...

117
00:13:15,942 --> 00:13:18,843
Stop talking like
you're humoring a child!

118
00:13:20,013 --> 00:13:21,037
I'm sorry...

119
00:13:22,282 --> 00:13:26,412
But you should know
this the most, Lord Orochimaru.

120
00:13:27,621 --> 00:13:29,987
Nobody can beat Kimimaro,

121
00:13:30,056 --> 00:13:32,547
no matter what hindrance
should appear.

122
00:13:37,330 --> 00:13:38,854
Thanks for saving me...

123
00:13:38,932 --> 00:13:42,732
Being able to do something like this;
very impressive.

124
00:13:43,036 --> 00:13:45,937
All I did was ride the sand
I'm always controlling.

125
00:13:46,840 --> 00:13:48,705
You just have to know how you use it.

126
00:13:52,445 --> 00:13:53,707
Lord Orochimaru...

127
00:13:56,349 --> 00:13:59,147
I'm sorry, Lord Orochimaru...

128
00:14:08,595 --> 00:14:11,462
At last... The destruction of
the Leaf will begin...

129
00:14:11,832 --> 00:14:15,598
Third Hokage...
I'll teach you a thing or two.

130
00:14:29,216 --> 00:14:30,615
Sorry to keep you waiting.

131
00:14:37,691 --> 00:14:39,921
What's the matter, Kimimaro?

132
00:14:41,728 --> 00:14:43,787
No... It's nothing.

133
00:14:56,209 --> 00:14:58,473
Even the Kazekage of
the Hidden Sand Village

134
00:14:59,012 --> 00:15:02,072
is no match against us.

135
00:15:05,652 --> 00:15:07,142
Of course...

136
00:15:08,421 --> 00:15:10,946
Kimimaro, it's thanks to you...

137
00:15:14,227 --> 00:15:15,251
Kimimaro!

138
00:15:15,428 --> 00:15:18,829
Kimimaro, so you can't go on, huh?

139
00:15:20,500 --> 00:15:23,401
I'm sorry, Lord Orochimaru.

140
00:15:34,981 --> 00:15:36,972
<i>If I can't be of use...</i>

141
00:15:39,686 --> 00:15:41,813
<i>then there's no significance</i>
<i>to my living.</i>

142
00:15:45,725 --> 00:15:47,920
How is your condition, Kimimaro?

143
00:15:49,029 --> 00:15:52,328
The "Destruction of the Leaf"
resulted in an unfortunate near miss.

144
00:15:53,099 --> 00:15:56,933
But the Sound Ninja Four
have gone to pick up a new vessel...

145
00:16:00,140 --> 00:16:03,598
Lord Orochimaru's new
"Vessel of Dreams."

146
00:16:07,314 --> 00:16:09,680
<i>Orochimaru's brainwashing, huh...?</i>

147
00:16:11,084 --> 00:16:12,711
<i>You're a pitiful guy...</i>

148
00:16:13,954 --> 00:16:16,582
You're wrong... Far from it!

149
00:16:17,324 --> 00:16:21,454
<i>There's no significance to living...</i>

150
00:16:23,897 --> 00:16:27,492
<i>But...you might be able to discover</i>
<i>something interesting</i>

151
00:16:27,567 --> 00:16:29,501
<i>by continuing to live...</i>

152
00:16:30,971 --> 00:16:34,304
<i>Like how you discovered that flower...</i>

153
00:16:36,443 --> 00:16:39,435
<i>Like how I discovered you.</i>

154
00:16:42,048 --> 00:16:45,575
<i>This is the "Earth" Curse Mark!</i>

155
00:16:46,319 --> 00:16:50,016
<i>With this... I can become</i>
<i>a part of you, Lord Orochimaru.</i>

156
00:16:50,657 --> 00:16:54,286
<i>Let's get everything, Kimimaro...</i>

157
00:16:54,661 --> 00:16:58,290
<i>And let's see the truth of</i>
<i>this world together.</i>

158
00:17:06,740 --> 00:17:09,641
<i>I'm going to discover</i>
<i>the truth of this world!</i>

159
00:17:10,844 --> 00:17:13,142
With Lord Orochimaru!

160
00:17:20,420 --> 00:17:23,218
He was a persistent guy,
but this is the end.

161
00:17:24,524 --> 00:17:26,651
He won't ever come out again.

162
00:17:27,761 --> 00:17:28,693
R-Right...

163
00:17:33,666 --> 00:17:34,792
I can't go on...

164
00:17:35,935 --> 00:17:36,993
We're getting off...

165
00:17:38,138 --> 00:17:39,765
It's not brainwashing!

166
00:17:41,574 --> 00:17:46,602
That person...
Lord Orochimaru understands me!

167
00:17:49,416 --> 00:17:52,579
What do you guys know?!

168
00:18:16,576 --> 00:18:17,838
He's dead...

169
00:18:21,548 --> 00:18:23,982
Could it be? Has Kimimaro...?

170
00:18:25,452 --> 00:18:28,979
The likes of Kimimaro makes
no difference now...

171
00:18:31,057 --> 00:18:35,221
Sasuke... I can hardly wait for him.

172
00:18:36,496 --> 00:18:40,296
He'll come here even by himself...

173
00:18:44,070 --> 00:18:46,163
I would have been totally hammered.

174
00:18:47,907 --> 00:18:49,272
That's not the case.

175
00:18:50,009 --> 00:18:52,341
My sensei said it often...

176
00:18:52,879 --> 00:18:54,904
Luck is also a part of strength.

177
00:18:55,515 --> 00:18:57,540
That backseat driver?

178
00:18:57,817 --> 00:18:59,717
He's not a backseat driver!

179
00:19:00,453 --> 00:19:01,477
It's because...

180
00:19:04,858 --> 00:19:06,723
I wasn't good enough at that time!

181
00:19:10,964 --> 00:19:13,330
I'm grateful for you saving me.

182
00:19:14,067 --> 00:19:17,332
But please don't talk like that
about my sensei!

183
00:19:19,739 --> 00:19:21,400
You, too...?

184
00:19:23,610 --> 00:19:25,134
When you feel that

185
00:19:25,211 --> 00:19:27,907
the honor of someone you revere
has been hurt,

186
00:19:28,314 --> 00:19:30,680
you yourself are hurt badly
and become enraged.

187
00:19:31,484 --> 00:19:33,714
The more important the person
you revere is to you,

188
00:19:33,786 --> 00:19:35,117
the greater the feeling...

189
00:19:36,322 --> 00:19:39,519
<i>The clan won't die out...</i>
<i>I'm not alone.</i>

190
00:19:40,059 --> 00:19:43,995
<i>I will remain inside</i>
<i>Lord Orochimaru's soul for all eternity.</i>

191
00:19:44,397 --> 00:19:48,834
<i>That person,</i>
<i>Lord Orochimaru, understands me!</i>

192
00:19:49,502 --> 00:19:51,970
<i>What do you guys know?!</i>

193
00:19:54,274 --> 00:19:57,072
Fighting for the sake of someone
important to you...

194
00:19:59,279 --> 00:20:04,216
He was also the same
as Naruto Uzumaki...

195
00:20:06,753 --> 00:20:10,280
But... the person who is important
to oneself

196
00:20:10,356 --> 00:20:12,847
might not always be "virtuous"

197
00:20:12,992 --> 00:20:14,220
I wonder...

198
00:20:14,727 --> 00:20:18,527
There's no way someone evil
can be thought of as an important person.

199
00:20:18,598 --> 00:20:22,694
No. Even if you know they're evil...

200
00:20:24,938 --> 00:20:27,065
People can't defeat solitude...

201
00:20:43,556 --> 00:20:45,023
Sasuke!

202
00:21:11,252 --> 00:21:13,652
<i>For the first time, I spoke to you</i>

203
00:21:13,721 --> 00:21:16,747
<i>And you smiled</i>

204
00:21:16,991 --> 00:21:19,289
<i>For the first time, I was able to speak</i>

205
00:21:19,360 --> 00:21:22,090
<i>In my own words</i>

206
00:21:22,162 --> 00:21:27,725
<i>Would you think it was</i>
<i>a bother if I approached you?</i>

207
00:21:28,002 --> 00:21:33,269
<i>Despite my doubts,</i>
<i>I worked up my courage</i>

208
00:21:33,540 --> 00:21:38,944
<i>My clumsy attempts with words</i>

209
00:21:39,146 --> 00:21:44,675
<i>You listened without turning away</i>

210
00:21:45,586 --> 00:21:50,853
<i>No wonder I get carried away by you</i>

211
00:21:51,258 --> 00:21:57,925
<i>But you don't feel anything for me, do you?</i>

212
00:21:58,432 --> 00:22:01,128
<i>I feel so sad</i>

213
00:22:01,201 --> 00:22:02,099
<i>But...</i>

214
00:22:02,169 --> 00:22:04,569
<i>For the first time, I spoke to you</i>

215
00:22:04,638 --> 00:22:07,607
<i>And you smiled</i>

216
00:22:07,741 --> 00:22:10,335
<i>For the first time, I was able to speak</i>

217
00:22:10,411 --> 00:22:13,403
<i>In my own words</i>

218
00:22:13,580 --> 00:22:15,912
<i>For the first time, I spoke to you</i>

219
00:22:15,983 --> 00:22:19,111
<i>And you smiled</i>

220
00:22:19,186 --> 00:22:21,654
<i>For the first time, I was able to speak</i>

221
00:22:21,722 --> 00:22:24,623
<i>In my own words</i>

222
00:22:24,758 --> 00:22:29,252
<i>For the first time, I spoke to you</i>

223
00:22:37,638 --> 00:22:39,037
You gotta be kidding me!

224
00:22:39,206 --> 00:22:41,333
What do you mean
"for achieving your goal"?!

225
00:22:41,508 --> 00:22:45,774
Orochimaru wants you
only as a "vessel"!

226
00:22:46,013 --> 00:22:48,607
There's no way
I can let you go to him!

227
00:22:49,650 --> 00:22:51,140
This is no joke!

228
00:22:51,485 --> 00:22:58,482
If you insist on going,
I have to take you back by force!

229
00:22:59,626 --> 00:23:01,924
Next episode: "A Cry on Deaf Ears"
